article.headline: Cal Poly-SLO 66, S. Dakota St. 62
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Shawn Lewis scored 21 points in leading Cal Poly to a 66-62 win over South Dakota State in a ESPNU BracketBuster game Saturday night. Chaz Thomas and Titus Shelton scored 18 and 10 points respectively for the Mustangs who improved to 7-17. Kai Williams led the Jackrabbits with 19 while Dale Moss scored 18 with the team falling to 12-17 overall. The Mustangs shot 48 percent from the floor and made 39 percent from long range. South Dakota State shot 41 percent, but made just 16 percent from beyond the arch.
